main event: A civilian in Cloverdale, Ohio reported seeing an orange-colored object in the western sky that appeared to move slightly and then disappear.
interesting points: The object was compared to the planet Venus but was described as a little larger.
The object appeared to twinkle and then just disappeared from view.
The Air Force concluded that the sighting was likely caused by the planet Venus, which was setting at the time of the observation.
The Air Force stated that no physical evidence is known to exist that would support the idea that unidentified flying objects are interplanetary vehicles.
The Air Force provided information about the hours of operation for the Air Force Museum, which may have exhibits related to UFOs and Project Blue Book.
sighted object: An orange-colored object in the sky
